  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Economic Resilience Support Project for most vulnerable Households (Displaced, Returnees and Host Fa</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to improve food security and living conditions of at least 500 most vulnerable households (displaced, returnees and host families) in Masisi territory through provision of food vouchers, through value vouchers for food (for access to immediate food needs) and the establishment of community-based Farmers&#x2019; Solidarity Groups (FSGs) who will be provided with improved seeds and tools (through value vouchers seed and tools fairs) for improved agricultural productivity. Crops from these fields will be used as a direct food supplement to the children in the targeted families and surpluses will be sold to meet other basic social needs of the targeted families.   
The food vouchers will be for one month for 500 most vulnerable households.</narrative>
  </description>
